HEADWORD: Placoid
<hw>Plac"oid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pla`x</grk>, <grk>plako`s</grk>, a tablet + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Platelike; having irregular, platelike, bony
scales, often bearing spines; pertaining to the placoids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Placoid
<hw>Plac"oid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Any fish having placoid scales, as the sharks.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>One of the Placoides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placoides</ent>⟦br⟧
